-- China Stocks Rise as Manufacturing Growth Signals Economy Gaining Strength
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-09-29T02:36:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/china-stocks-rise-as-manufacturing-growth-signals-economy-gaining-strength.html
China’s stocks rose, led by banks
and commodity producers, after manufacturing expanded faster
this month, signaling economic growth is accelerating.  The Shanghai Composite Index added 0.8 percent to 2,632.27
at 10:32 a.m. local time. The purchasing managers’ index for
China rose to 52.9 in September from 51.9 in the previous month,
according to data released by HSBC Holdings Plc and Market
Economics.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  